# SDK в†’ Standalone App Migration Plan

Convert the Learning Module SDK + example app into a fully independent standalone React Native application on a new `independent` git branch.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Branch strategy**: We will create a new git branch `independent` from the current branch. On this branch, the entire repo structure will be overhauled вЂ” SDK packaging removed, example app promoted to root, and all code reorganized.

> [!WARNING]
> **Destructive on branch**: The `independent` branch will remove SDK-specific files (`src/sdk/`, `src/multiply.tsx`, monorepo configs, builder-bob setup). The `main` branch is untouched.

> [!CAUTION]
> **Android/iOS native projects**: Moving `example/android/` and `example/ios/` to root requires careful handling of path references in `settings.gradle`, `build.gradle`, `Podfile`, etc. We'll verify these post-move.

## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q1**: Should I also update the `app.json` display name from `LearningSDKExample` to `Learning App` (or similar)?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q2**: The current example app's babel config uses `react-native-builder-bob/babel-config` which is SDK-specific. The standalone app will use a standard `@react-native/babel-preset` config. Is that acceptable?

